              "key": "prabhu joseph",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=prabhu+joseph&avatarId=38454",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=prabhu+joseph&avatarId=38454",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=prabhu+joseph&avatarId=38454",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=prabhu+joseph&avatarId=38454"
              },
              "displayName": "Prabhu Joseph",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "body": "Thanks [~SanjayKumarSahu] for reporting the issue. Currently Tez Splits is based on AMRMClient#getAvailableResources which is the HeadRoom based on How Much the Queue/Job User/Partition Limit is set. Changing Split calculation based on Total YARN Cluster Resource will lead to high Task Parallelism and Tez Job waiting for other queue/user/Partition resources which it won't get.\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n{code:java}\r\n  /**\r\n   * Get the currently available resources in the cluster.\r\n   * A valid value is available after a call to allocate has been made\r\n   * @return Currently available resources\r\n   */\r\n  public abstract Resource getAvailableResources();\r\n{code}",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=prabhujoseph",
              "name": "prabhujoseph",
              "key": "prabhu joseph",
